az (acetaminophen-benzhydrocodone)." KemPharm, Inc, Coralville, IA.[2] Liu S-J, Wang RI "Case report of barbiturate-induced enhancement of methadone metabolism and withdrawal syndrome." Am J Psychiatry 141 (1984): 1287-8[3] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[4] "Product Information. Duragesic Transdermal System (fentanyl)." Janssen Pharmaceutica, Titusville, NJ.[5] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[6] "Product Information. Butorphanol Tartrate (butorphanol)." Apotex Corporation, Weston, FL.[7] "Product Information. Ionsys (fentanyl)." Ortho McNeil Pharmaceutical, Raritan, NJ.[8] Bell J, Seres V, Bowron P, Lewis J, Batey R "The use of serum methadone levels in patients receiving methadone maintenance." Clin Pharmacol Ther 43 (1988): 623-9[9] "Product Information. Zohydro ER (HYDROcodone)." Zogenix, Inc, San Diego, CA.[10] "Product Information. OxyContin (oxycodone)." Purdue Frederick Company, Norwalk, CT.[11] "Product Information. Olinvyk (oliceridine)." Trevena Inc, Chesterbrook, PA.', 1767365205);
